Save it because chances are you will never see this reel again.

Cross-country adventure with a purpose! 🗽🌆 East to West: When Our Parents Visited the U.S. 🇺🇸❤️

We wanted to give them a trip that had everything—city buzz, natural wonders, glitz, and golden coast calm. Here’s how we planned it:

Pro tip : We had 10 days—made it work by taking 6 days off + 2 weekends.

📅Day 1–3 | New York City
Started in NYC—stayed in the Financial District. Walked miles, saw the classics, and made sure Mom got her skyline photo with the Statue of Liberty in the background.

📅Day 3 | NYC ➝ Niagara Falls (Road Trip)
Rented from Avis (PSA: Amazon employees get great discounts!).
The 8-hour drive was long, but we wanted to give them the classic American road trip experience. Worth every mile.

📅Day 3–5 (Morning) | Niagara Falls
Stayed at a peaceful BnB near the Falls. Slower pace, stunning views, and that “wow” moment when they saw the falls up close.

📅Day 5 | Niagara ➝ Vegas (Flight)
Took a midday flight, reached Vegas by evening. Checked in at The Strip—gave them a taste of all that sparkle and spectacle.

📅Day 5–7 | Las Vegas
Checked out major shows and hotels, night strolls under neon lights, and Vegas downtown including Fremont Street

Day 7 | Vegas ➝ Los Angeles (Drive)
Hit the road to LA—drove into Inglewood. Had a pit stop at Seven Magic Mountains—bright, bold, and so Instagrammable.

Day 7–9 | Los Angeles
Explored LA at our pace—sunshine, street food, and quiet moments at the beach. A perfect wrap-up.

Day 9 | LA ➝ Seattle (Flight)
Went to Universal Studios and then evening flight back to Seattle. A full-circle moment—home sweet home, with memories made coast to coast.

🌟 Newest Indian fine-dine experience in Redmond – Jashn! 🇮🇳

Brought to you by the creators of Chutneys and Fusion India, this place draws inspiration from the regal culinary heritage of Lucknow – beautifully showcasing the timeless elegance of Mughlai and Awadhi cuisines. 👑🍽️

From the crispy, tangy Chandni Chowk Chaska 🌱 to the melt-in-your-mouth Rajma ki Galouti 😋 and the creamy Banarasi Dum Aloo 🥔 – every dish is a flavor bomb! 💥 Oh, and don’t even get me started on the bold Thecha Paneer 🌶️ and the Kathal Champaran🎃

And the royal vibes don’t end there – even the water is served in fancy pital ke glass (brass glasses) 🥂 that make you feel like you’re dining in a palace. ✨

Honestly, yahan toh jana banta hai! Because this isn’t just eating out – it’s living your royal fantasy! 👑

💫 Tag someone who would love this royal experience!
📍 Where: Jashn, Redmond

Okay, THIS just became one of the most magical things I’ve ever done in Seattle
Romantic ❤️ Scenic ✨ A little bit boujee 🥂
And totally unforgettable 💫

We took the @kenmoreair scenic seaplane tour over the city…
and for 30 minutes ⏳, it felt like we were floating inside the skyline 🏙️
Like walking between the buildings—above the water 🌊, past the rooftops 🏢
Insane.

It wasn’t just beautiful—it felt ✨ intimate ✨ and surreal
The city looked like a literal painting 🎨
And I swear I got goosebumps mid-flight 🥹

This is the kind of thing you do once, and talk about forever 🗣️

I’m all about comfort fashion- so no matter where I am, chikankari suits and kurtis are my summer staples. Breezy, beautiful, and always feel like home ☀️🤍

Every summer, I flaunt my chikankari kurtas all over the PNW- and this summer is no less! Don’t believe me? Check my stories- I’ve reshared my summer fashion fits there!

Also, yes- I buy all of them right here in the US. I’ve stopped buying months in advance from India because fashion moves fast, and I’d end up not wearing half of it. This way? Less waste, more wear.

Big thanks to @theniraethnics for the variety you offer and this stunning piece. I seriously can’t wait to show off all the other beautiful pieces I picked from here. Do check them out🥰

NYC with parents? Don’t make the same mistake I did! 🚗😩 I rented a car and got 2 parking tickets 💸 Meanwhile, my parents conquered the city using the subway like pros! 🚂👏

Staying at @moxydowntownnyc Downtown (Financial District) was a game-changer. We walked everywhere, and only took the subway once. 🏙️👣

Here’s our 2.5-day NYC itinerary:

✨ Day 1: Desi vibes in NJ, Charging Bull, Wall Street, and WTC Memorial
✨ Day 2: Statue of Liberty, Brooklyn Bridge, DUMBO, and Times Square
✨ Day 3: Summit One Vanderbilt and a spontaneous drive to Niagara Falls!

Save this for your next NYC family trip! Especially if it’s your parents’ first time. Trust me, skip the car and book central. 🚫🚗

✨ Fusion food but make it Indian. ✨

Took my parents on a 10-day East + West Coast trip hoping they’d try different cuisines—but desi parents being desi, only wanted Indian food 😅 So when I stumbled upon Id-ally in LA, it was a game-changer.

They serve fusion South Indian food that’s as delicious as it is wholesome—think stuffed idlis, dosa tacos, and even chocolate dosa! 💥 Everything is made fresh, packed with flavor, and surprisingly light. Guilt-free indulgence? Yes please.

📍Pickup-ready in under 30 minutes
🛵 Also available on Grubhub, Uber Eats, DoorDash, Postmates, AND ChowNow—no excuses not to try it!

We grabbed ours on the way to Santa Monica Pier and got stopped by strangers asking where it was from. That’s how good it was.

🌱 Authentic. Creative. Healthy. Unmissable.
Save this spot for your LA trip—and tag your dosa buddy below! 👇

✨We all know Indian moms are often son-obsessed. But my mom, she has only one child- ME!! And she made sure I had the best education📖, lifestyle😇, and wardrobe💃. 

🤩That’s the beauty of a mom-daughter love - it comes with no expectations, no strings attached. She let me fly, rise, speak up and dream 💭 while saying, ‘Tu hamari fikr mat kar, jo mann ho wahi karo.’

That’s why these moms deserve the world - for their unconditional love, for not making their daughters feel guilty about the life choices they make.

To all the Indian daughters who, despite societal pressure, continue to show up for their parents, even after marriage, more power to you💪. Your love breaks generational patterns, and your strength rewrites expectations. 

Yes read that again 🌸❤️
